    "Details of ED, NoED, and Gibberish are provided in Table 3. 2.",
    "We save the tweets labelled as \"Evidence of Depression,\" which we call DSD-Clinician-ED-Tweets, (Arrow 8 in Fig. 5).",
    "We later use those to harvest depression symptoms-related tweets. 3.",
    "Next, we separate 70% of the tweets from DSD-Clinician-Tweets-Original dataset and create DSD-Clinician-Tweets-Original-Train dataset for training our first version of DSD model, called DSD-Clinician-1 and the rest 30% of the tweets are used as an SSL evaluation set, also called, DSD-Clinician-Tweets-Original-Test, (Arrows 5 and 7 in the Fig. 5).",
    "We will use this evaluation set all through our SSL process to measure the performance of SSL, i.e., whether it helps increase accuracy for DSD task or not."
